glossed as: "wife, this originally referred not to a real wife, but someone who was in a secondary 'pirangura, betrotherd' relationship, which had nothing to do with actual marriage. It also appears to have referred generally to someone who was of one's own generation and of the opposite moiety, yet not actually married to the speaker"
